The paper deals with learning hash codes for image retrieval, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of deep learning techniques for this purpose suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on retrieval for tumor assessment, which suggests that it may also be relevant to medical imaging (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
